===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Loveland had a population of 36 people, with 14 households and 7 families residing in the community.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A46785&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A46785&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 915.4 inhabitants per square mile (353.5/km<sup>2</sup>), and there were 17 housing units at an average density of 432.3 per square mile (166.9/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

The median age was 43.7 years. 16.7% of residents were under age 18, and 16.7% were 65 years of age or older. By broader age group, 22.2% of residents were under age 20, 2.8% were from 20 to 24, 30.6% were from 25 to 44, and 27.8% were from 45 to 64. The gender makeup was 58.3% male and 41.7% female. For every 100 females, there were 140.0 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 200.0 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020PL"/>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A46785&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

Of the 14 households, 0.0% had children under the age of 18 living in them. Of all households, 21.4% were married-couple households, 0.0% were cohabiting-couple households, 35.7% were households with a male householder and no spouse or partner present, and 42.9% were households with a female householder and no spouse or partner present. About 50.0% were non-family households, 42.9% were made up of individuals, and 21.4% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of the 17 housing units, 17.6% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020PL"/>

